x = 0
x = 2\pi
(\underbrace{1 - \cos 2x}_{\text{upper curve}}\quad - \underbrace{0}_{\text{lower curve}}) \,dx = (1 - \cos 2x)\,dx
\begin{align}\int_0^{2\pi} (1 - \cos 2x)\,dx \quad & = \quad \int_0^{2\pi} \,dx \quad - \quad \int_0^{2\pi} \cos 2x\, dx\\ \\ & = x\Big\vert_0^{2\pi} \quad -\quad \dfrac 12 \sin 2x\Big\vert_0^{2\pi}\\ \\ & = (2\pi - 0) - \frac 12 (\sin(4\pi) - \sin(0))\\ \\  & = (2\pi - 0) - \frac 12(0 - 0) \\ \\ & = 2\pi\end{align}
\displaystyle\int^{2\pi}_01-\cos(2x)dx=x+\sin(2x)|_0^{2\pi}=2\pi+\sin4\pi\,-0-\sin0=2\pi.
